Let's start with a Stack. A Stack is a data structure that contains a collection of elements which can be accessed by their position in the Stack. The following image depicts a Stack.

<a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/657jB.png" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><IMAGE></a>

In the image, the top element can be accessed by its position (1). The last element can be accessed by its position (0). Note that, elements in the Stack can be inserted or removed from the end to the beginning. This operation is called Push and Pop.

Let's consider the following code:

```
// stack is an Array of size 10
class Stack {
    int array[10];
    int top = -1;
    int size = 0;
    void push(int data){
        if(top == 0) {
            size++;
        }
        array[++top] = data;
    }
    int pop(){
        return array[top--];
    }
}
```

