How can I fix this Java code to avoid a NullPointerException? "public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String name = null;
        System.out.println(name.length());
    }
}"

answer:
You can avoid the NullPointerException by checking if name is null before calling its length() function. The following code will work:

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String name = null;
        if (name != null) {
            System.out.println(name.length());
        }
    }
}
